<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Noun">Noun</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Noun"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Stairway_Measurements.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Stairway_Measurements.svg/220px-Stairway_Measurements.svg.png" decoding="async" width="220" height="162" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Stairway_Measurements.svg/330px-Stairway_Measurements.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Stairway_Measurements.svg/440px-Stairway_Measurements.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="475" data-file-height="350"></a><figcaption>diagram of stairs, showing the <i>run</i> (<a href="#English:_stair">sense 18.2</a>)</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Stocking_run.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Stocking_run.jpg/110px-Stocking_run.jpg" decoding="async" width="110" height="288" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Stocking_run.jpg/165px-Stocking_run.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e8/Stocking_run.jpg/220px-Stocking_run.jpg 2x" data-file-width="402" data-file-height="1054"></a><figcaption>Stockings with a <b>run</b> (<a href="#English:_knit">sense 21</a>) in them</figcaption></figure>
<p><span class="headword-line"><strong class="Latn headword" lang="en">run</strong> (<i>plural</i> <b class="Latn form-of lang-en p-form-of" lang="en"><a href="/wiki/runs#English" title="runs">runs</a></b>)</span>
</p>
<ol><li>Act or instance of running, of moving rapidly using the feet.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">I just got back from my morning <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><b>2012</b> June 9, Owen Phillips, “Euro 2012: Netherlands 0-1 Denmark”, in <cite>BBC Sport</cite>‎<sup><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18138777">[12]</a></sup>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Krohn-Dehli took advantage of a lucky bounce of the ball after a battling <b>run</b> on the left flank by Simon Poulsen, dummied two defenders and shot low through goalkeeper Maarten Stekelenburg's legs after 24 minutes.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li>Act or instance of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/hurry#English" title="hurry">hurrying</a> (to or from a place) <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">not necessarily on foot</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span>; <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/dash#English" title="dash">dash</a> or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/errand#English" title="errand">errand</a>, <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/trip#English" title="trip">trip</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><b>1759</b>, N. Tindal, <i>The Continuation of Mr Rapin's History of England</i>, volume 21 (continuation volume 9), page 92:
<dl><dd><span class="q-hellip-sp"> </span><span class="q-hellip-b">[</span>…<span class="q-hellip-b">]</span><span class="q-hellip-b"> </span> and on the 18th of January this squadron put to sea. The first place of rendezvous was the boy of port St. Julian, upon the coast of Patagonia, and all accidents were provided against with admirable foresight. Their <b>run</b> to port St. Julian was dangerous <span class="q-hellip-sp"> </span><span class="q-hellip-b">[</span>…<span class="q-hellip-b">]</span><span class="q-hellip-b"> </span></dd></dl></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><b>1987</b> April 25, Kim Westheimer, “A Black Gay Fireman's Story”, in <cite>Gay Community News</cite>, page 1:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Jackson said the white firefighters attempted to make him and other Black firefighters miss <b>runs</b> by not waking them up along with everyone else.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul>
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">I need to make a <b>run</b> to the store.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>A pleasure trip.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">Let's go for a <b>run</b> in the car.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1842</b></span> December – <b>1844</b> July, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Dickens" class="extiw" title="w:Charles Dickens">Charles Dickens</a>, chapter 30, in <cite><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin_Chuzzlewit" class="extiw" title="w:Martin Chuzzlewit">The Life and Adventures of Martin Chuzzlewit</a></cite>, London: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chapman_%26_Hall" class="extiw" title="w:Chapman &amp; Hall">Chapman and Hall</a>,<span class="q-hellip-sp">&nbsp;</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">[</span></span><span title="193, Piccadilly">…</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">]</span></span><span class="q-hellip-b"></span>, published <span class="None" lang="und">1844</span>, <small><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/title/977517776">→OCLC</a></small>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">And I think of giving her a <b>run</b> in London for a change.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/flight#English" title="flight">Flight</a>, instance or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/period#English" title="period">period</a> of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/flee#English" title="flee">fleeing</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>2006</b></span>, Tsirk Susej, <cite>The Demonic Bible</cite>, <small><a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1411690737" title="Special:BookSources/1411690737">→ISBN</a></small>, page <span class="None" lang="und">41</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">During his <b>run</b> from the police, he claimed to have a metaphysical experience which can only be described as “having passed through an abyss.”</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/migration#English" title="migration">Migration</a> <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">of fish</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span>.</li>
<li>A group of fish that migrate, or ascend a river for the purpose of spawning.</li>
<li>A literal or figurative path or course for movement relating to:
<ol><li>A (regular) <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/trip#English" title="trip">trip</a> or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/route#English" title="route">route</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The bus on the Cherry Street <b>run</b> is always crowded.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><b>1977</b>, <i>Star Wars</i> (film)
<dl><dd>You've never heard of the Millennium Falcon? It's the ship that made the Kessel <b>Run</b> in less than twelve parsecs.</dd></dl></li></ul></li>
<li>The <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/route#English" title="route">route</a> taken while running or skiing.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">Which <b>run</b> did you do today?</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="/wiki/skiing#Noun" title="skiing">skiing</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> bobsledding</span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A single trip down a hill, as in <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/skiing#English" title="skiing">skiing</a> and <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/bobsledding#English" title="bobsledding">bobsledding</a>.</li>
<li>The distance sailed by a ship.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">a good <b>run</b>; a <b>run</b> of fifty miles</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/voyage#English" title="voyage">voyage</a>.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">a <b>run</b> to China</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/trial#English" title="trial">trial</a>.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The data got lost, so I'll have to perform another <b>run</b> of the experiment.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/mathematics#English" title="mathematics">mathematics</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> <a href="/wiki/computing#Noun" title="computing">computing</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/execution#English" title="execution">execution</a> of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/program#English" title="program">program</a> or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/model#English" title="model">model</a>
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">This morning's <b>run</b> of the SHIPS statistical model gave Hurricane Priscilla a 74% chance of gaining at least 30 knots of intensity in 24 hours, reconfirmed by the HMON and GFS dynamical models.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/video_game#English" title="video game">video games</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/speedrunning#English" title="speedrunning">speedrunning</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/playthrough#English" title="playthrough">playthrough</a>, or attempted playthrough; a session of play.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">This was my first successful <b>run</b> without losing any health.</i></div></dd>
<dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">That NPC bugged out and killed my <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl></li></ol></li>
<li>Unrestricted use. <span class="use-with-mention">Only used in <i class="Latn mention" lang="en"><a href="/wiki/have_the_run_of#English" title="have the run of">have the run of</a></i></span>.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">He can have the <b>run</b> of the house.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>An <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/enclosure#English" title="enclosure">enclosure</a> for an animal; a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/track#English" title="track">track</a> or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/path#English" title="path">path</a> along which something can travel.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">He set up a rabbit <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="senseid" id="English:_landholding" data-senseid="landholding"><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Australian_English" class="extiw" title="w:Australian English">Australia</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Zealand_English" class="extiw" title="w:New Zealand English">New Zealand</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A <a href="/wiki/rural#Adjective" title="rural">rural</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/landholding#English" title="landholding">landholding</a> for <a href="/wiki/farm#Verb" title="farm">farming</a>, usually for <a class="mw-selflink-fragment" href="#Verb">running</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/sheep#English" title="sheep">sheep</a>, and <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/operate#English" title="operate">operated</a> by a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/runholder#English" title="runholder">runholder</a>.</li>
<li>State of being current; currency; popularity.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><b>1715</b> June 5 (Gregorian calendar), <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Addison" class="extiw" title="w:Joseph Addison">Joseph Addison</a>, “The Free-holder: No. 45. Wednesday, May 25. <span style="font-style: normal;">[</span>1715.<span style="font-style: normal;">]</span>”, in <cite>The Works of the Right Honourable Joseph Addison, Esq;<span class="q-hellip-sp">&nbsp;</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">[</span></span><span title="In Four Volumes.">…</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">]</span></span><span class="q-hellip-b"></span></cite>, volume IV, London: <span class="q-hellip-sp"> </span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">[</span></span><span title="Printed for">…</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">]</span></span><span class="q-hellip-b"> </span> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacob_Tonson" class="extiw" title="w:Jacob Tonson">Jacob Tonson</a>,<span class="q-hellip-sp">&nbsp;</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">[</span></span><span title="at Shakespear’s-Head, over-against Katharine-street in the Strand.">…</span><span class="q-hellip-b"><span style="font-style: normal;">]</span></span><span class="q-hellip-b"></span>, published <span class="None" lang="und">1721</span>, <small><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/title/1056445272">→OCLC</a></small>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">It is impossible for detached papers[...] to have a general <b>run</b>, or long continuance, if they are not diversified[...].</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li>Continuous or sequential
<ol><li>A continuous period (of time) marked by a trend; a period marked by a continuing trend.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">I’m having a <b>run</b> of bad luck.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><b>1782</b> <span style="font-variant:small-caps;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frances_Burney" class="extiw" title="w:Frances Burney">Frances Burney</a></span> <i><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cecilia_(Burney_novel)" class="extiw" title="w:Cecilia (Burney novel)">Cecilia</a></i>
<dl><dd>“<span class="q-hellip-sp"> </span><span class="q-hellip-b">[</span>…<span class="q-hellip-b">]</span><span class="q-hellip-b"> </span>had had the preceding night an uncommon <i><b>run</b> of luck</i>”.</dd></dl></li></ul>
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">He went to Las Vegas and spent all his money over a three-day <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1795–1797</b></span>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edmund_Burke" class="extiw" title="w:Edmund Burke">Edmund Burke</a>, “<span class="maintenance-line" style="color: #777777;">(please specify |letter=1 to 4)</span>”, in <cite><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Letters_on_a_Regicide_Peace" class="extiw" title="w:Letters on a Regicide Peace">[Letters on a Regicide Peace]</a></cite>, London: [<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivington_(publishers)" class="extiw" title="w:Rivington (publishers)">Rivington</a>]:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">They who made their arrangements in the first <b>run</b> of misadventure [...] put a seal on their calamities.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><b>2011</b> June 28, Piers Newbery, “Wimbledon 2011: Sabine Lisicki beats Marion Bartoli”, in <cite>BBC Sport</cite>‎<sup><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/tennis/13946420.stm">[13]</a></sup>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">German wildcard Sabine Lisicki conquered her nerves to defeat France's Marion Bartoli and take her amazing Wimbledon <b>run</b> into the semi-finals.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li>A series of tries in a game that were successful.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">If our team can keep up their strong defense, expect them to make a <b>run</b> in this tournament.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>A production quantity (such as in a factory).
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">Yesterday we did a <b>run</b> of 12,000 units.</i></div></dd>
<dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The book’s initial press <b>run</b> will be 5,000 copies.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>The period of showing of a play, film, TV series, etc.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The <b>run</b> of the show lasted two weeks, and we sold out every night.</i></div></dd>
<dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">It is the last week of our French cinema <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><b>1856</b> February, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Babington_Macaulay" class="extiw" title="w:Thomas Babington Macaulay">[Thomas Babington] Macaulay</a>, “<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oliver_Goldsmith" class="extiw" title="w:Oliver Goldsmith">Oliver Goldsmith</a>”, in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Flower_Ellis" class="extiw" title="w:Thomas Flower Ellis">T[homas] F[lower] E[llis]</a>, editor, <cite>The Miscellaneous Writings and Speeches of Lord Macaulay</cite>, new edition, London: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longman" class="extiw" title="w:Longman">Longman, Green, Reader, &amp; Dyer</a>, published <span class="None" lang="und">1871</span>, <small><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.worldcat.org/title/30956848">→OCLC</a></small>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">A canting, mawkish play [...] had an immense <b>run</b>.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#slang" title="Appendix:Glossary">slang</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A period of extended (usually <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/daily#English" title="daily">daily</a>) drug use.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1964</b></span>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Velvet_Underground" class="extiw" title="w:The Velvet Underground">The Velvet Underground</a>, <cite>Heroin</cite>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">And I'll tell ya, things aren't quite the same / When I'm rushing on my <b>run</b>.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1975</b></span>, Lloyd Y. Young, Mary Anne Koda-Kimble, Brian S. Katcher, <cite>Applied Therapeutics for Clinical Pharmacists</cite>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Frank Fixwell, a 25 year-old male, has been on a heroin "<b>run</b>" (daily use) for the past two years.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><b>1977</b>, Richard P. Rettig, Manual J. Torres, Gerald R. Garrett, <i>Manny: a criminal-addict's story</i>, Houghton Mifflin Harcourt (HMH) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780395248386" title="Special:BookSources/9780395248386">→ISBN</a>
<dl><dd>I was hooked on dope, and hooked bad, during this whole period, but I was also hooked behind robbery. When you're on a heroin <b>run</b>, you stay loaded so long as you can score.</dd></dl></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>2001</b></span>, Robin J. Harman, <cite>Handbook of Pharmacy Health Education</cite>, Pharmaceutical Press, <small><a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780853694717" title="Special:BookSources/9780853694717">→ISBN</a></small>, page <span class="None" lang="und">172</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">This can develop quite quickly (over a matter of hours) during a cocaine <b>run</b> or when cocaine use becomes a daily habit.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>2010</b></span>, Robert DuPont, <cite>The Selfish Brain: Learning from Addiction</cite>, Hazelden Publishing, <small><a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781592859535" title="Special:BookSources/9781592859535">→ISBN</a></small>, page <span class="None" lang="und">158</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">DA depletion leads to the crash that characteristically ends a cocaine <b>run</b>.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/card_game#English" title="card game">card games</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A sequence of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/cards#English" title="cards">cards</a> in a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/suit#English" title="suit">suit</a> in a card game.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/music#English" title="music">music</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/rapid#English" title="rapid">rapid</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/passage#English" title="passage">passage</a> in <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/music#English" title="music">music</a>, especially along a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/scale#English" title="scale">scale</a>.</li></ol></li>
<li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="senseid" id="English:_liquid" data-senseid="liquid">A flow of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/liquid#English" title="liquid">liquid</a>; a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/leak#English" title="leak">leak</a>.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The constant <b>run</b> of water from the faucet annoys me.</i></div></dd>
<dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">a <b>run</b> of must in wine-making</i></div></dd>
<dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">the first <b>run</b> of sap in a maple orchard</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content">chiefly eastern <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Midland_American_English" class="extiw" title="w:Midland American English">North Midland US</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> especially <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ohio" class="extiw" title="w:Ohio">Ohio</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pennsylvania" class="extiw" title="w:Pennsylvania">Pennsylvania</a><span class="ib-comma">,</span> West Virginia</span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A small <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/creek#English" title="creek">creek</a> or part thereof. <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">Compare Southern US <i><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/branch#English" title="branch">branch</a></i> and New York and New England <i><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/brook#English" title="brook">brook</a></i>.</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span>
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">The military campaign near that creek was known as "The battle of Bull <b>Run</b>".</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/quick#English" title="quick">quick</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pace#English" title="pace">pace</a>, faster than a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/walk#English" title="walk">walk</a>.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">He broke into a <b>run</b>.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ol><li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content">of horses</span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A fast <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/gallop#English" title="gallop">gallop</a>.</li></ol></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="/wiki/banking#Noun" title="banking">banking</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A sudden series of demands on a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/bank#English" title="bank">bank</a> or other financial institution, especially characterised by great withdrawals.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">Financial insecurity led to a <b>run</b> on the banks, as customers feared for the security of their savings.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>Any sudden large <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/demand#English" title="demand">demand</a> for something.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">There was a <b>run</b> on Christmas presents.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li>Various horizontal dimensions or surfaces
<ol><li>The top of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/step#English" title="step">step</a> on a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/staircase#English" title="staircase">staircase</a>, also called a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/tread#English" title="tread">tread</a>, as opposed to the <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/rise#English" title="rise">rise</a>.</li>
<li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="senseid" id="English:_stair" data-senseid="stair"> The horizontal length of a set of stairs</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/construction#English" title="construction">construction</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/horizontal#English" title="horizontal">Horizontal</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/dimension#English" title="dimension">dimension</a> of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/slope#English" title="slope">slope</a>.</li></ol></li>
<li>A standard or unexceptional group or category.
<dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">He stood out from the usual <b>run</b> of applicants.</i></div></dd></dl></li>
<li><span class="use-with-mention"><span class="Latn" lang="en">In sports</span></span>
<ol><li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/baseball#English" title="baseball">baseball</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/score#English" title="score">score</a> when a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/runner#English" title="runner">runner</a> touches all <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/base#English" title="base">bases</a> legally; the act of a runner scoring.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/cricket#English" title="cricket">cricket</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The act of passing from one <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/wicket#English" title="wicket">wicket</a> to another; the <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/point#English" title="point">point</a> scored for this.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/American_football#English" title="American football">American football</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> A running play.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd>[...] <i>one of the greatest <b>runs</b> of all time.</i></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>2003</b></span>, Jack Seibold, <cite>Spartan Sports Encyclopedia</cite>, page <span class="None" lang="und">592</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Aaron Roberts added an insurance touchdown on a one-yard <b>run</b>.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/golf#English" title="golf">golf</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The movement communicated to a golf ball by running it.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/golf#English" title="golf">golf</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The distance a ball travels after touching the ground from a stroke.</li>
<li>The distance drilled with a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/bit#English" title="bit">bit</a>, in oil drilling.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1832</b></span>, <cite>Records and Briefs of the United States Supreme Court</cite>, page <span class="None" lang="und">21</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Well, when you compare the cone type with the cross roller bit, you get a longer <b>run</b>, there is less tendency of the bit to go flat while running in various formations. It cleans itself better.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li></ol></li>
<li class="mw-empty-elt"></li><li class="senseid" id="English:_knit" data-senseid="knit"> A line of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/knit#English" title="knit">knit</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/stitches#English" title="stitches">stitches</a> that have <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/unravelled#English" title="unravelled">unravelled</a>, particularly in a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/nylon#English" title="nylon">nylon</a> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/stocking#English" title="stocking">stocking</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><div class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="en">I have a <b>run</b> in my stocking.</i></div></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1975</b></span>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joni_Mitchell" class="extiw" title="w:Joni Mitchell">Joni Mitchell</a> (lyrics and music), “The Boho Dance”, in <cite>The Hissing of Summer Lawns</cite>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">A camera pans the cocktail hour / Behind a blind of potted palms / And finds a lady in a Paris dress / With <b>runs</b> in her nylons</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/nautical#English" title="nautical">nautical</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/stern#English" title="stern">stern</a> of the underwater body of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/ship#English" title="ship">ship</a> from where it begins to curve upward and inward.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="/wiki/mining#Noun" title="mining">mining</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> The horizontal distance to which a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/drift#English" title="drift">drift</a> may be carried, either by licence of the <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/proprietor#English" title="proprietor">proprietor</a> of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/mine#English" title="mine">mine</a> or by the nature of the formation; also, the direction which a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/vein#English" title="vein">vein</a> of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/ore#English" title="ore">ore</a> or other substance takes.</li>
<li>A pair or set of <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/millstone#English" title="millstone">millstones</a>.</li></ol>

<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: See also"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">computer science</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span><span class="ib-colon sense-qualifier-colon">:</span> <span class="Latn" lang="en"><a href="/wiki/trajectory#English" title="trajectory">trajectory</a></span></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Adjective">Adjective</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Adjective"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span class="headword-line"><strong class="Latn headword" lang="en">run</strong> (<i>not <a href="/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#comparable" title="Appendix:Glossary">comparable</a></i>)</span>
</p>
<ol><li>In a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/liquid#English" title="liquid">liquid</a> state; <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/melted#English" title="melted">melted</a> or <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/molten#English" title="molten">molten</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><i>Put some <b>run</b> butter on the vegetables.</i></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1921</b></span>, L. W. Ferris, H. W. Redfield, W. R. North, “The Volatile Acids and the Volatile Oxidizable Substances of Cream and Experimental Butter”, in <cite>Journal of Dairy Science</cite>, volume 4, page <span class="None" lang="und">522</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Samples of the regular <b>run</b> butter were sealed in 1 pound tins and sent to Washington, where the butter was scored and examined.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/cast#English" title="cast">Cast</a> in a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/mould#English" title="mould">mould</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1735</b></span>, Thomas Frankz, <cite>A tour through France, Flanders, and Germany: in a letter to Robert Savil</cite>, page <span class="None" lang="und">18</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">[...] the Sides are generally made of Holland's Tiles, or Plates of <b>run</b> Iron, ornamented variously as Fancy dictates, [...]</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><b>1833</b>, <i>The Cabinet Cyclopaedia: A treatise on the progressive improvement and present state of the Manufactures in Metal</i>, volume 2, <i>Iron and Steel</i> (printed in London), page 314:
<dl><dd>Vast quantities are cast in sand moulds, with that kind of <b>run</b> steel which is so largely used in the production of common table-knives and forks.</dd></dl></li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#c." title="Appendix:Glossary">c.</a></i>&nbsp;<b>1839</b>, (Richard of Raindale, <i>The Plan of my House vindicated</i>, quoted by) T. T. B. in the <i>Dwelling of Richard of Raindale, King of the Moors</i>, published in <i>The Mirror</i>, number 966, 7 September 1839, page 153:
<dl><dd>For making tea I have a kettle,</dd>
<dd>Besides a pan made of <b>run</b> metal;</dd>
<dd>An old arm-chair, in which I sit well —</dd>
<dd>The back is round.</dd></dl></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/exhaust#English" title="exhaust">Exhausted</a>; <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/deplete#English" title="deplete">depleted</a> <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">especially with "down" or "out"</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span>.</li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content">of a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/zoology#English" title="zoology">zoology</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/travelled#English" title="travelled">Travelled</a>, <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/migrated#English" title="migrated">migrated</a>; having made a <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/migration#English" title="migration">migration</a> or a spawning <a href="#Noun">run</a>.
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1889</b></span>, Henry Cholmondeley-Pennell, <cite>Fishing: Salmon and Trout</cite>, fifth edition, page 185:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">The temperature of the water is consequently much higher than in either England or Scotland, and many newly <b>run</b> salmon will be found in early spring in the upper waters of Irish rivers where obstructions exist.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1986</b></span>, Arthur Oglesby, <cite>Fly fishing for salmon and sea trout</cite>, page <span class="None" lang="und">15</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">It may be very much a metallic appearance as opposed to the silver freshness of a recently <b>run</b> salmon.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li>
<li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>2005</b></span>, Rod Sutterby, Malcolm Greenhalgh, <cite>Atlantic Salmon: An Illustrated Natural History</cite>, page <span class="None" lang="und">86</span>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="en">Thus, on almost any day of the year, a fresh-<b>run</b> salmon may be caught legally somewhere in the British Isles.</span></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/smuggled#English" title="smuggled">Smuggled</a>.
<dl><dd><i><b>run</b> brandy</i></dd></dl></li></ol>

<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Usage_notes">Usage notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: Usage notes"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/transcription" title="transcription">Transcriptions</a> of Mandarin into the Latin script often do not distinguish between the critical <a href="/wiki/tonal" title="tonal">tonal</a> differences employed in the Mandarin language, using words such as this one without indication of tone.</li></ul>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Etymology_2">Etymology</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=29" title="Edit section: Etymology"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>

Please add to it, or discuss it at the <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:Etymology_scriptorium" title="Wiktionary:Etymology scriptorium">Etymology scriptorium</a>.)</span>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Noun_2">Noun</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=30" title="Edit section: Noun"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span class="headword-line"><strong class="Latn headword" lang="nrf">run</strong>&nbsp;<span class="gender"><abbr title="masculine gender">m</abbr></span> (<i>plural</i> <b class="Latn form-of lang-nrf p-form-of" lang="nrf"><a href="/wiki/runs#Norman" title="runs">runs</a></b>)</span>
</p>
<ol><li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content"><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/nautical#English" title="nautical">nautical</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span> <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/beam#English" title="beam">beam</a> <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">of a ship</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span></li></ol>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Norwegian_Nynorsk">Norwegian Nynorsk</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Norwegian Nynorsk"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Alternative_forms_2">Alternative forms</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: Alternative forms"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><span class="Latn" lang="nn"><a href="/wiki/ron#Norwegian_Nynorsk" title="ron">rón</a> <span class="gender"><abbr title="feminine gender">f</abbr></span>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=rjon&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="rjon (page does not exist)">rjón</a> <span class="gender"><abbr title="neuter gender">n</abbr></span></span> <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">dialectal</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Etymology_3">Etymology</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=33" title="Edit section: Etymology"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>From <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Norse" class="extiw" title="w:Old Norse">Old Norse</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="non"><a href="/wiki/r%C3%BAn#Old_Norse" title="rún">rún</a></i>&nbsp;<span class="gender"><abbr title="feminine gender">f</abbr></span> <span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">(</span><span class="mention-gloss-double-quote">“</span><span class="mention-gloss">rune, secret</span><span class="mention-gloss-double-quote">”</span><span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">)</span>, from <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proto-Norse_language" class="extiw" title="w:Proto-Norse language">Proto-Norse</a></span> <i class="Runr mention" lang="gmq-pro"><a href="/wiki/%E1%9A%B1%E1%9A%A2%E1%9A%BE%E1%9B%9F#Proto-Norse" title="ᚱᚢᚾᛟ">*ᚱᚢᚾᚢ</a></i> <span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">(</span><span lang="gmq-pro-Latn" class="mention-tr tr Latn">*runu</span> <span class="ts mention-ts Latn">/⁠rūnu⁠/</span><span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">)</span>, from <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proto-Germanic_language" class="extiw" title="w:Proto-Germanic language">Proto-Germanic</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="gem-pro"><a href="/wiki/Reconstruction:Proto-Germanic/r%C5%ABn%C5%8D" title="Reconstruction:Proto-Germanic/rūnō">*rūnō</a></i>. Akin to <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_language" class="extiw" title="w:English language">English</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="en"><a href="/wiki/roun#English" title="roun">roun</a></i> <span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">(</span><span class="mention-gloss-double-quote">“</span><span class="mention-gloss">secret; rune</span><span class="mention-gloss-double-quote">”</span><span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">)</span>.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Pronunciation_3">Pronunciation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=34" title="Edit section: Pronunciation"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a><sup>(<a href="/wiki/Appendix:Norwegian_Nynorsk_pronunciation" title="Appendix:Norwegian Nynorsk pronunciation">key</a>)</sup>: <span class="IPA">/rʉːn/</span></li></ul>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Noun_3">Noun</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Noun"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span class="headword-line"><strong class="Latn headword" lang="nn">run</strong>&nbsp;<span class="gender"><abbr title="feminine gender">f</abbr></span> (<i>definite singular</i> <b class="Latn" lang="nn"><a href="/wiki/runa#Norwegian_Nynorsk" title="runa">runa</a></b>, <i>indefinite plural</i> <b class="Latn" lang="nn"><a href="/wiki/runer#Norwegian_Nynorsk" title="runer">runer</a></b>, <i>definite plural</i> <b class="Latn" lang="nn"><a href="/w/index.php?title=runene&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="runene (page does not exist)">runene</a></b>)</span>
</p>
<ol><li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/witchcraft#English" title="witchcraft">witchcraft</a>
<span class="HQToggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a role="button" tabindex="0">quotations&nbsp;▼</a></span><dl><dd><span class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="nn">taka <b>run</b> på ein</i> ― <span class="e-translation">use <b>witchcraft</b> on someone</span></span></dd></dl>
<ul style="display: none;"><li><div class="citation-whole"><span class="cited-source"><span class="None" lang="und"><b>1911</b></span>, Torkell Mauland, <cite>Trolldom</cite> [<cite><span class="e-translation">Witchcraft</span></cite>], <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nb.no/items/33bf1df79dc1f8a7c19f0725c534a954?page=152">page <span class="None" lang="und">147</span></a>:</span><dl><dd><div class="h-quotation"><span class="Latn e-quotation cited-passage" lang="nn">Han [Johan] hadde den hausten lege i trætta med Omund Horpestad um ein kvernastad, og daa hadde han truga med at han skulde taka <b>run</b> paa Omund. So sa i minsto Omund Horpestad daa han bad lensmannen, Mons Øksnavad, stemna Johans til Haugs-tinget ²⁷/₁₁ 1650.</span><dl><dd><span class="e-translation">He [Johans] had that autumn been in a quarrel with Omund Horpestad about a milling place, and had then threatened with using <b>witchcraft</b> on Omund. This is at least what Omund Horpestad told when he asked the sheriff, Mons Øksnavad, to subpoena Johans to the Haugating at 27th November 1650.</span></dd></dl></div></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li>
<li><span class="usage-label-sense"><span class="ib-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content">chiefly in the <a href="/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#plural" title="Appendix:Glossary">plural</a></span><span class="ib-brac">)</span></span>:
<ol><li>secret or magic aids</li>
<li><a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/rune#English" title="rune">rune</a> <span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">(</span><span class="ib-content qualifier-content">a letter of runic alphabet</span><span class="ib-brac qualifier-brac">)</span>
<span class="nyms-toggle" style="margin-left: 5px;"><a>synonym&nbsp;▲</a></span><dl><dd><span class="nyms synonym"><span class="defdate">Synonym:</span> <span class="Latn" lang="nn"><a href="/wiki/rune#Norwegian_Nynorsk" title="rune">rune</a></span>&nbsp;<span class="gender"><abbr title="feminine gender">f</abbr></span></span></dd></dl></li></ol></li></ol>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="References">References</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=38" title="Edit section: References"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://aasen.ordboki.no/ord/Runer">“Runer”</a> in Ivar Aasen (1873) <i>Norsk Ordbog med dansk Forklaring</i></li></ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Old_English">Old English</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=39" title="Edit section: Old English"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Etymology_4">Etymology</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=40" title="Edit section: Etymology"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>From <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proto-West_Germanic_language" class="extiw" title="w:Proto-West Germanic language">Proto-West Germanic</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="gmw-pro"><a href="/wiki/Reconstruction:Proto-West_Germanic/r%C5%ABnu" title="Reconstruction:Proto-West Germanic/rūnu">*rūnu</a></i>. Cognate with the <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Saxon" class="extiw" title="w:Old Saxon">Old Saxon</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="osx"><a href="/wiki/runa#Old_Saxon" title="runa">rūna</a></i>, <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_High_German" class="extiw" title="w:Old High German">Old High German</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="goh"><a href="/wiki/runa#Old_High_German" title="runa">rūna</a></i> (<span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_language" class="extiw" title="w:German language">German</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="de"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Raun&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Raun (page does not exist)">Raun</a></i>), <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Norse" class="extiw" title="w:Old Norse">Old Norse</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="non"><a href="/wiki/r%C3%BAn#Old_Norse" title="rún">rún</a></i>, and <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gothic_language" class="extiw" title="w:Gothic language">Gothic</a></span> <i class="Goth mention" lang="got"><a href="/wiki/%F0%90%8D%82%F0%90%8C%BF%F0%90%8C%BD%F0%90%8C%B0#Gothic" title="𐍂𐌿𐌽𐌰">𐍂𐌿𐌽𐌰</a></i> <span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">(</span><span lang="got-Latn" class="mention-tr tr Latn"><a href="/wiki/runa#Gothic" title="runa">runa</a></span><span class="mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren">)</span>.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Pronunciation_4">Pronunciation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=41" title="Edit section: Pronunciation"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Vietnamese">Vietnamese</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=55" title="Edit section: Vietnamese"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Etymology_5">Etymology</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=56" title="Edit section: Etymology"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>From <span class="etyl"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proto-Vietic_language" class="extiw" title="w:Proto-Vietic language">Proto-Vietic</a></span> <i class="Latn mention" lang="mkh-vie-pro"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Reconstruction:Proto-Vietic/-ru%CB%90n&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Reconstruction:Proto-Vietic/-ruːn (page does not exist)">*-ruːn</a></i>.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Pronunciation_6">Pronunciation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=57" title="Edit section: Pronunciation"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<ul><li>(<i><a href="/wiki/H%C3%A0_N%E1%BB%99i" title="Hà Nội">Hà Nội</a></i>) <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a><sup>(<a href="/wiki/Appendix:Vietnamese_pronunciation" title="Appendix:Vietnamese pronunciation">key</a>)</sup>: <span class="IPA">[zun˧˧]</span></li>
<li>(<i><a href="/wiki/Hu%E1%BA%BF" title="Huế">Huế</a></i>) <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a><sup>(<a href="/wiki/Appendix:Vietnamese_pronunciation" title="Appendix:Vietnamese pronunciation">key</a>)</sup>: <span class="IPA">[ʐun˧˧]</span></li>
<li>(<i><a href="/wiki/H%E1%BB%93_Ch%C3%AD_Minh_City" title="Hồ Chí Minh City">Hồ Chí Minh City</a></i>) <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a><sup>(<a href="/wiki/Appendix:Vietnamese_pronunciation" title="Appendix:Vietnamese pronunciation">key</a>)</sup>: <span class="IPA">[ɹʊwŋ͡m˧˧]</span></li>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Verb_4">Verb</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=run&amp;action=edit&amp;section=58" title="Edit section: Verb"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p><span class="headword-line"><strong class="Latn headword" lang="vi">run</strong> <a href="/wiki/Wiktionary:Vietnamese_transliteration" title="Wiktionary:Vietnamese transliteration">•</a> (<span lang="vi-Latn" class="headword-tr tr Latn" dir="ltr"><span class="Hani" lang="vi"><a href="/wiki/%E6%83%87#Vietnamese" title="惇">惇</a>, <a href="/wiki/%E6%85%B5#Vietnamese" title="慵">慵</a>, <a href="/wiki/%E6%95%A6#Vietnamese" title="敦">敦</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=%F0%A2%B9%88&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="𢹈 (page does not exist)">𢹈</a></span></span>)</span>
</p>
<ol><li>to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/tremble#English" title="tremble">tremble</a>, to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/shiver#English" title="shiver">shiver</a> (due to cold)</li></ol>

</p>
<ol><li>to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/crumble#English" title="crumble">crumble</a>; to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/shatter#English" title="shatter">shatter</a>
<dl><dd><span class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="yo">Ó ti <b>rún</b> wómúwómú</i> ― <span class="e-translation">It has completely <b>crumbled</b></span></span></dd></dl></li>
<li>to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/chew#English" title="chew">chew</a>
<dl><dd><span class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="yo">Mo fẹ́ <b>rún</b> obì</i> ― <span class="e-translation">I want to <b>chew</b> a kola nut</span></span></dd></dl></li>
<li>to <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/crinkle#English" title="crinkle">crinkle</a>; to be <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/wrinkled#English" title="wrinkled">wrinkled</a>
<dl><dd><span class="h-usage-example"><i class="Latn mention e-example" lang="yo">Ṣé ẹ̀wù mi ti <b>rún</b>?</i> ― <span class="e-translation">Are my clothes <b>creased</b>?</span></span></dd></dl></li></ol>
